<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-53-0443 </DOCNO><TEXT>The author offers a different view of monopoly which is based upon thepremise that all major energy industries are natural monopolies. He saysthat we hear repeatedly that we are an increasing unit cost industrywhich, if true, probably does mean that all the dire predictions of ourdemise are accurate. Our greatest challenge is to become a decliningunit cost industry or at least a stable unit cost industry if we areto preform what the authors thinks is the real purpose of a monopoly- supplying energy at a stable price over long periods of time. The authordiscusses how monopolies do this.</TEXT></DOC>